data.text:
White Fang:

White Fang is the independent, volatile protagonist in Jack London's novel White Fang. He is born in the wild but then becomes the property of Grey Beaver, until Grey Beaver sells him to Beauty Smith. Beauty is only interested in how much money White Fang can make him as a fighting dog. His business scheme nearly kills White Fang. Fortunately, White Fang is saved by Weedon Scott, a passerby who witnesses White Fang's near-death experience in the arena. Weedon takes White Fang home with him to California.
